  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Umeme Capex</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The investment program will enable Umeme to boost loss reduction and increase connections and as such enhance the quality, availability and reliability of electricity supply to consumers, businesses and industries, thereby improving the overall energy efficiency of the Ugandan distribution system and reducing local and emergency diesel based supplies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Umeme Limited (Umeme, or the Company), Ugandas largest electricity distribution company, plans to invest up to US$ 440 Million in Ugandas distribution system over the course of the next years until and including 2018. Out of this amount the Company expects to raise debt financing of up to US$ 170 Million (the Project), while the remainder is to be financed through internally generated funds. The investment is aimed at improving the systems operational performance including distribution losses and collection rates amongst others. Umeme holds a concession for electricity distribution in Uganda until 2025 and is presently majority owned by Actis LLP.</narrative>
  </description>
